&lt;p&gt;Rowan ward is a busy 29 bedded acute female general surgical ward, specialising in patients with gynaecology, breast and ENT including caring for patients with a tracheostomy &amp; laryngectomy).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;All successful candidates will be mentored and will be supported in their position having the opportunity to further their academic career by being put forward for the surgical and mentoring courses. You will be supported by the Practice Development Nurse and the Matron for Surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Care Quality Commission has recognised the significant improvements made at Whipps Cross in their latest visit and the 2018 Staff Survey results showed staff have seen many improvements in their working lives. With our passionate staff and commitment to safe and compassionate care, we know Whipps Cross will keep getting better and better. We’d love you to join us on our journey to good and outstanding. Come and be part of the Whipps Cross family where you can make a difference.&lt;/p&gt;
